(341, 1, '2015-03-05 06:38:01', '2015-03-05 06:38:01', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]Melissa and James were married four years ago and disaster struck when their wedding photographer did not show up to their wedding! Karen Alsop from Emerald Eye Photography in Victoria decided to help utilise a wedding photography retreat to allow James and Melissa to finally get the wedding photos they deserved. I was privileged to be attending the wedding retreat and here is a small selection of the photos I captured for this special couple. Melissa and James also utilised the opportunity to renew their vows. I hope these images form their wedding album for them to hand down to their children.[/vc_column_text][uxb_divider style="special"][vc_gallery images="333,334,335,336,337,338,339,340" type="image_grid" grid_style="square" img_size="full" columns="col4" onclick="link_image" interval="5" show_bullets="true"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Their Wedding Photographer Didn''t Turn Up To The Wedding!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '331-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-05 06:38:01', '2015-03-05 06:38:01', '', 331, 'http://localhost/samantha-ohlsen-photography/331-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(342, 1, '2015-03-05 06:48:55', '2015-03-05 06:48:55', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/1"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>After the wedding</h3>\r\nFind the photos you DO like and get them on your wall and in an album\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Foffbeatbride.com%2F2012%2F02%2Fwhat-to-do-with-wedding-photos&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNGrOa99qA_eXU2IIeCpjTzCdaXM1w" target="_blank"><strong>What do you do with your wedding photos after the wedding?</strong></a>\r\n\r\nWhat did you do with your photos after the wedding? Do you have them up in your house? Do you have an album? If you... [<a href="http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Foffbeatbride.com%2F2012%2F02%2Fwhat-to-do-with-wedding-photos&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNGrOa99qA_eXU2IIeCpjTzCdaXM1w" target="_blank"><strong>more</strong></a>]\r\n\r\nAfter spending money on wedding photos, please please please do not leave them in the digital nebulas and interwebs. When historians (or *cough* family members) dig through your attic, old broken hard drives with wedding photos will be useless.\r\n\r\nEven if you''re disappointed with your wedding photos, find the few you <em>do</em> like, and print them up. If it''s literally only a couple photos, cherish them, print them, and hang them on the wall.\r\n\r\nIf you can find a few more, make an album. The process of choosing photos to print might help you re-live all the excitement of your wedding. You may never go through the 1,000 digital images that you hate on your hard drive, but you''ll look at the certain photos that you <em>do</em> like in your album, or that one photo on your wall for years to come.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Top 10 Tips To Get Great Wedding Photos – Part Six After The Wedding', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'top-10-tips-to-get-great-wedding-photos-part-six-after-the-wedding', '', '', '2015-03-05 06:48:55', '2015-03-05 06:48:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/samantha-ohlsen-photography/?p=342', 11, 'post', '', 0),
